Lingua-Identify-CLD

These are Perl bindings to CLD, the Compact Language Detection library
from Google/Chrome.

While CLD is not available as a standard package with a standard build
system, I am shiping the code in the tarball. For details on the
library check
  http://code.google.com/p/chromium-compact-language-detector/

Note that you will require a C compiler to build the library and the bindings.


ARCHITECTURE SUPPORT
 - currently this module is not building correctly on PPC.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Lingua::Identify::CLD

You can also look for information at:

    Git repository and ticket tracker (report bugs here)
        http://github.com/ambs/Lingua-Identify-CLD

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Lingua-Identify-CLD

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Lingua-Identify-CLD

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Lingua-Identify-CLD/


